Tool Name

StarUML

Installation Steps

Open a web browser and go to the official StarUML website

Download the installer suitable for your operating system (Windows/Linux/macOS)

Run the installer and follow on-screen instructions

Complete the installation process

Configuration Steps

Launch StarUML after installation

Create a new project

Select UML 2 as the modeling language

Save the project with the name
Blood_Bank_Management_System.mdj

Use the toolbox to create:

Use Case Diagram

Class Diagram

Sequence Diagram

Usage in Project

StarUML is used to design and document UML diagrams included in the SRS appendices.

Option 2: Visual Paradigm â€“ Installation & Configuration
Tool Name

Visual Paradigm (Community Edition)

Installation Steps

Visit the official Visual Paradigm website

Download the Community Edition

Run the installer and complete the setup process

Launch the application after installation

Configuration Steps

Create a new project

Choose UML Project

Name the project as
Blood Bank Management System

Configure diagram types such as:

Use Case Diagram

Class Diagram

Activity Diagram

Usage in Project

Visual Paradigm is used to model UML diagrams and export them for documentation.

System Requirements

Operating System: Windows 10 or above

RAM: Minimum 4 GB

Disk Space: Minimum 500 MB

Internet: Required for download

Conclusion

The CASE tool (StarUML / Visual Paradigm) was successfully installed and configured. It will be used throughout the project to create UML diagrams that support system analysis and design of the Blood Bank Management System.
